      "writtenOn": "2018-04-20T20:34:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "skylarkstruct is trying to remove its to_proto()/to_json() methods; according to the internal bug pointed to by https://github.com/google/skylark/blob/11b496306ff83d01ad34c57ed772f22ef69d8a75/skylarkstruct/struct.go#L224,\n\n\u003e The .to_proto and .to_json fields of a struct should be moved to a library function (or deleted) since they raise an ambiguity: in what order are attributes sought: fields or methods first? struct fields should take precedence. Having to_proto on a struct is a mistake: struct should really be an \"unconstrained namespace\"\n\nI\u0027m not sure if this should also apply to Message, however.",
      "revId": "52487c20c746423a6869701d12071cdbdc7a6b5a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3c9e0865_343126d1",
        "filename": "skylark/skylarkproto/methods.go",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 28,
      "author": {
        "id": 1177675
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-04-20T20:34:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\"to_text\" is somewhat ambiguous; these days, a proto3 is as likely to be represented as JSON as it is pbtext, and both are technically \"text\". Maybe this method should take a format parameter, or have a more explicit name like \"to_pbtext\" or \"to_proto_text\".",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 28,
        "startChar": 32,
        "endLine": 28,
        "endChar": 39
      },
      "revId": "52487c20c746423a6869701d12071cdbdc7a6b5a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "18fa9195_1ca29187",
        "filename": "skylark/skylarkproto/methods.go",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 28,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-04-20T22:05:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Renamed to \u0027to_pbtext\u0027. This is also now a function that lives in \u0027protobuf\u0027 module, so the usage from skylark scripts would look like:\n\n  m \u003d some_pb.Message(....)\n  proto.to_pbtext(m)",
      "parentUuid": "3c9e0865_343126d1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 28,
        "startChar": 32,
        "endLine": 28,
        "endChar": 39
      },
      "revId": "52487c20c746423a6869701d12071cdbdc7a6b5a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3b368dc5_a3f3e932",
        "filename": "skylark/skylarkproto/methods.go",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 28,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-04-20T22:05:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Good point. I also thought about possibility of collision between field names and \"standard\" method names. I initially decided to keep it inside the message because there\u0027s no other natural namespace to put it into.\n\nI\u0027ve now added \"proto\" module that has a collection of functions (currently only 1) to work with protobuf messages. Embedders of this library will have to expose the content of this module to the script environment.",
      "parentUuid": "55120991_df229cec",
      "revId": "52487c20c746423a6869701d12071cdbdc7a6b5a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "22bfd39d_405abca2",
        "filename": "skylark/skylarkproto/methods.go",
