    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "254184c9_44d1ab1e",
        "filename": "skylark/skylarkproto/methods.go",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 37,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-04-20T22:05:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, I really don\u0027t want to reimplement proto serialization from scratch in Skylark... Especially considering possibility that we\u0027ll use binary serialization someday too (e.g. when pushing configs to luci-config or something).\n\nThe downside is that skylark scripts know only about proto types compiled inside the go binary that hosts the interpreter, so we won\u0027t be able to have some universal interpreter that can work with arbitrary protos.",
      "parentUuid": "22bfd39d_405abca2",
